article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. -- — Sean Hansen scored 15 points as Cornell beat Colgate 77-64 on Saturday night. Hansen went 6 of 9 from the field for the Big Red (10-2). Chris Manon scored 14 points while going 5 of 9 from the field and 3 of 7 from the free-throw line, and added four steals. Guy Ragland Jr. was 5-of-7 shooting and 2 of 3 from the free-throw line to finish with 12 points. The Raiders (6-7) were led by Braeden Smith, who posted 12 points and five assists. Ryan Moffatt added 11 points for Colgate. In addition, Jeff Woodward finished with nine points and nine rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
